The Association of Coastal and Waterways Communities of Nigeria (ACWCN) has warned of expected health hazards following the recent explosion of a floating Production, Storage and Off-Loading vessel Ukpokti Terminus, Escavos, Wado City, Delta State. The vessel was carrying over 50,000 barrels of crude oil.   Family sues for compensation over property acquisition     2023: Bello inaugurates youth campaign wing in Southwest     Senator, council chair lose mum   President of ACWCN Comrade Bawo Ighomi called on the Federal Government to act fast to prevent any pollution and epidemic on people around the vicinity. Ighomi insisted that relevant agencies like National Oil Spillage Detection and Response Agency (NOSDRA) and Federal Ministry of Environment should act fast to ensure the environment is devoid of health pollution for humans and animals. He said: “Disturbing reports reaching us indicate that this explosion has started to show signs of wrecking health havoc on both human and domestic animals, and if nothing is done to remedy the threatening situation, it may degenerate faster.”